        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Extreme Risk Protection Order and Violence Prevention Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a new grant program to help states and Indian tribes implement extreme risk protection order laws. </p> <p>Extreme risk protection order laws, or red flag laws, generally allow certain individuals (e.g., law enforcement officers or family members) to petition a court for a temporary order that prohibits an at-risk individual from purchasing and possessing firearms.</p> <p>The bill also expands the categories of persons who are prohibited from receiving, possessing, shipping, or transporting a firearm or ammunition. Specifically, it adds a new category of prohibited persons: persons who are subject to an extreme risk protection order. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
